Text: This week should be Sprint for all of us, but I had to focus on my milestone for INFO202.
I have spent three days at the lab to solve the java problems.
Of course, there are still some I have to deal with them, but the deadline is on Monday 5 pm.
I hope I will figure out what are the solutions.
What about the project.
Our project goals were as below for this week: .
1 / web scrapping - Nene prepared the whole code to extract the data from the greyhound race website and connected them for testing with her local data tables in MySQL.
Now we have to focus on dividing all data according to our tables and connect them with our final database in a proper way.
2 / preparing the database - we were waiting for Georgine, who should make ERD and database in SQL.
Finally, we got partial ERD.
Because we didn't want to be stuck, I have prepared the ERD directly into MySQL and converted into a database.
- This database connects with the domain, which we have for our testing for This project.
From this stage, the next step would be preparing the visualisation for displaying the data.
3 / draft project for the final visualization / the tables - Yoko prepared the first short basic template.
Now it should be extended and adapted to the client's expectations and our database.
4 / test - if it is working or not - we have tested partially what works and whatnot.
But it was nothing at this point to show to the client.
We have tested with Nene the standard connection between the database and our temporary domain if we can work on it together.
I have prepared the manual instruction for the rest of the team what they have to install and how they can log in to the domain and database.
I spend a lot of time to learn how to connect all the small elements together.
I know much more right now, but still, a lot of things are black magic.
For example, this part how to extract the data via R, MySQL by pressing the button on the domain or set the time to extract the data automatically at 2 am.
I don't understand this part and need more explanation - looking for it via websites is very difficult, and even if I found something, it is unclear.
I struggle with this a lot.
Instead of having fewer and fewer tasks to do, I have the impression that we have more and more.
Our primary goals for next week: 1/ extract the historical data from greyhound websites2/ improve database3/ visualisation4/ find the connection between domain and R5/ find the alternative solution.

Nothing - this week showed the truth.
